    Motion

    • Overview
    • Choreography
    • Code

    The Carbon motion package empowers consistent cadence and movement of elements across digital experiences.

    If youâ€™re using 

    @carbon/react

    Usage

    The 

    @carbon/motion
    Copy to clipboard
    package enables you to access motion curves and durations built for the IBM Design Language in Sass. You can access these values directly from the package by writing the following:

    @use '@carbon/motion';
    .selector {
      // Set `transition-timing-function` directly
      @include motion.motion(standard, productive);
    

      // Alternatively
      transition: opacity motion.motion(standard, productive);
    

      // Or use a duration
    Copy to clipboard

    JavaScript

    If youâ€™re using 

    @carbon/motion
    Copy to clipboard
    as a JavaScript dependency, we export our easings and a function called 
    motion
    Copy to clipboard
    that you can use. For example:

    // CommonJS
    const { easings, motion } = require('@carbon/motion');
    Copy to clipboard

    You can also include this as a JavaScript module:

    // ESM
    import { easings, motion } from '@carbon/motion';
    

    motion('standard', 'productive'); // Returns a string `cubic-bezier()` function
    Copy to clipboard

    Configuration

    You can configure parts of the 

    @carbon/motion
    Copy to clipboard
    package with Sass Modules. For example, you can change the 
    $prefix
    Copy to clipboard
    used by writing the following:

    @use '@carbon/motion' with (
      $prefix: 'custom-prefix'
    );
    Copy to clipboard

    For a full list of options that you can configure, check out the table below.

    OptionDescriptionDefault
    $prefix
    Copy to clipboard
    		The prefix that is used in selectors, CSS Custom Properties, etc.
